channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Should Trump Choose J.D. Vance As His VP?
Tennessee sued over law banning adults from helping minors get abortions without parental consent
item.description: A lawsuit was filed Monday seeking to stop a Tennessee law that would prohibit adults from helping minors obtain an abortion without parental approval.

item.title: Christina Bobb to Newsmax: Trump to Be 'Strategic' in Upcoming Debate
item.description: Republican National Committee attorney Christina Bobb provided insights into former President Donald Trump's anticipated debate strategy during a Monday appearance on Newsmax's "Prime News." Bobb hinted at a potential shift in Trump's well-known dynamic and aggressive...

item.title: Kasie Hunt's Husband Called Out for Celebrating Trump's Mugshot, Reacts Poorly
GOP lines up culture war-heavy spending bills targeting military abortions, drag shows
item.description: House Republicans are seeking to include provisions on abortion, transgender health care, drag performers, and DEI in this year's appropriations bills.

item.title: Minn. GOP Chair to Newsmax: Trump Could Carry State; 1st Time Since '72
item.description: Minnesota Republican Party Chairman David Hahn told Newsmax on Monday that not since former President Richard Nixon has a Republican carried Minnesota in a general election, but former President Donald Trump could change that.

item.title: Julian Assange Saga Ends; Guilty Plea Traded For Freedom
Squad member faces ouster from Congress as New York, Colorado and Utah hold primaries on Tuesday
item.description: Rep. Jamaal Bowman of New York, a member of the progressive & diverse Squad, may be ousted in a Democratic primary Tuesday that spotlights the party's deep divisions over the Israel-Hamas war in Gaza

item.title: Netflix Special: Nazi Getaway Like 'Hitler's Mar-a-Lago'
item.description: A new six-part docuseries about Adolf Hitler and the Third Reich features a segment about the dictator's holiday getaway in the Bavarian Alps, with a contributor likening it to "Hitler's Mar-a-Lago."

item.title: Home Run: Texas Rangers Earn Plaudits After 'Pride Night' Stance Prompts Fresh Round of Woke Fretting
US v Trump: Defense to claim due process violations made in FBI's Mar-a-Lago raid
item.description: Former President Trump's defense team will argue that evidence obtained during a raid on Mar-a-Lago was privileged communications between attorney and client,.

item.title: Biden: Kenya Now a Non-NATO Ally
item.description: On Monday, President Joe Biden sent a memo to Secretary of State Antony Blinken declaring that Kenya is now a "Major Non-NATO Ally." The memo coincides with reports on Monday that Kenyan police are heading to Haiti.

item.title: CNN: Desperately Trying to Make Sure They Do Their Part in Protecting Joe Biden During This Week's Debate
Why the big debate question is not Biden’s stamina but Trump’s discipline
item.description: The first debate of the 2024 Presidential Election season will be underway soon. Are both President Biden and Donald Trump up for the challenge?

item.title: Rep. Mace to Newsmax: Bowman, AOC 'Mentally Unhinged'
item.description: Rep. Nancy Mace, R-S.C., said the rhetoric coming out of the profanity-laced rally held by "Squad" member Rep. Jamaal Bowman, D-N.Y., and his rapping sidekick, Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, D-N.Y., over the weekend was "dangerous."
